{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/reset-wordpress-file-permissions/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jack Harner","description":"Jack Harner is a Freelance Web Developer & E-Commerce Consultant based in Denver, Colorado. Shopify, BigCommerce, WordPress Dev & More.","author":"@jackharner","siteUrl":"https://jackharner.com"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Somehow I continuously run into File Permissions Issues while working with WordPress, so this is primarily just a reference for myself. For whatever reason, things can get pretty hectic, and you've probably ran into a similar issue if you've ever seen a \"Permission Denied\" error, or if WordPress asks you for your FTP Connection Information to update a plugin.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 492px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 112.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"WordPress asking for Connection Information\"\n        title=\"WordPress asking for Connection Information\"\n        src=\"/static/bed1aeac20e55f178ab525719878f31c/5c6e9/connection.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bed1aeac20e55f178ab525719878f31c/5a46d/connection.png 300w,\n/static/bed1aeac20e55f178ab525719878f31c/5c6e9/connection.png 492w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 492px) 100vw, 492px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Sometimes it's just best to reset everything back to the way Apache needs it to be to run smoothly: <code class=\"language-text\">775</code> on folders, and <code class=\"language-text\">664</code> on files.</p>\n<p>Run the following 3 terminal commands from the root of your WordPress install (the folder containing your <code class=\"language-text\">wp-config.php</code> file):</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=jack data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=jack data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=jack data-host=localhost></span></span><span class=\"token function\">chown</span> www-data:www-data <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-R</span> * <span class=\"token comment\"># Set Apache's www-data user as the owner</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">find</span> <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-type</span> d <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-exec</span> <span class=\"token function\">chmod</span> <span class=\"token number\">775</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\"># Change folder permissions to rwxrwxr-x</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">find</span> <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-type</span> f <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-exec</span> <span class=\"token function\">chmod</span> <span class=\"token number\">664</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\"># Change file permissions to rw-rw--r--</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm sure future me is thanking \"now\" me for writing this down so I can stop googling it. You're welcome future me!</p>","excerpt":"Somehow I continuously run into File Permissions Issues while working with WordPress, so this is primarily just a reference for myself. For whatever…","wordCount":{"words":128},"frontmatter":{"date":"July 19, 2021","updated":null,"title":"Reset WordPress File Permissions","subtitle":"","tags":["WordPress","Automation","Code Snippets"],"featuredImage":{"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/jackharner-gatsby/jackharner-gatsby/content/blog/reset-wordpress-file-permissions/featuredImage.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#082828","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/20435/featuredImage.png","srcSet":"/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/ea847/featuredImage.png 750w,\n/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/4a806/featuredImage.png 1080w,\n/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/e2aad/featuredImage.png 1366w,\n/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/20435/featuredImage.png 1920w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/57584/featuredImage.webp 750w,\n/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/984df/featuredImage.webp 1080w,\n/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/4a276/featuredImage.webp 1366w,\n/static/743cf2f79a767cb799303a916f197138/9c00f/featuredImage.webp 1920w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.6666666666666666}}},"ogImage":{"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/jackharner-gatsby/jackharner-gatsby/content/blog/reset-wordpress-file-permissions/ogImage.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#080808","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/c8d9e119cd317313dff1d61849657981/b5380/ogImage.png","srcSet":"/static/c8d9e119cd317313dff1d61849657981/a0e1b/ogImage.png 300w,\n/static/c8d9e119cd317313dff1d61849657981/86184/ogImage.png 600w,\n/static/c8d9e119cd317313dff1d61849657981/b5380/ogImage.png 1200w","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/c8d9e119cd317313dff1d61849657981/c7da1/og